quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  40,8,"Our Lord, admit them to the everlasting Gardens You have promised them and those of their fathers and spouses and progeny that were righteous. Surely You alone are Most Mighty, Most Wise;",footnotes:180950:1,footnotes:180951:2
  40,9,"and guard them against all ills. He whom You guard against ills on that Day, to him You have surely been Most Merciful. That is the great triumph.”",footnotes:180952:1,footnotes:180953:2
  40,10,"It will be announced to the unbelievers (on the Day of Resurrection): “Surely Allah's abhorrence of you when you were called to believe but you disbelieved was greater than is your abhorrence of yourselves today.”",footnotes:180954:1